Trusted Digital Assistants (TDA) are processing agents with embedded local storage agent capabilitiess for DID IDs associated with People, Organizations, Things, and Marketplaces. Processing Agents and Storage Agents are associated with DID IDs associated with Objects. Verifiable Data Registry (VDR) Agents are for managing entries stored in a variety of trusted global registries.

*did:colors returns DID Method Registration
*did:colors:red returns the DID Document associated with the DID Identifier (did:colors:red)

**did:colors:red causes the DID Agent to return the Swagger definition (or equivalent) for the DID Agent associated with the default (or overriden) URI of the Service EndPoint Entry for the specified DID Identifier (did:colors:red)

***did:colors:red causes the DID Agent to return the properties (claims) for the DID Object associated with the specificed DID Identifier (did:colors:red) as a Structured Credential from Decentralized Storage
Creatable/Deletable Entities
- DID Method Registry Entries - DID Method Registrations
- DID Documents

- DID Service Endpoint Entries (in DID Document) - DID Compute Agent deployment onto Agent Hosts (identified by a DID Service Endpoint Entry) - DID Credential Storage Agent deployment onto Agent Hosts (identified by a DID Service Endpoint Entry) - DID Verification Agent deployment onto Agent Hosts (identified by a DID Service Endpoint Entry)
- CredentialSubject Claims (Updateable)
- Verification Keys (DID Documents) - Verification Keys (Structured Credentials)

did:colors:red requests that the DID Identifier is to be verified by a Verification Agent identified by a Verification Agent Service Endpoint in the DID Document associated with the DID Identifier (did:colors:red) according to the Verification Method.
